# Zoom Clone - Cursor AI Instructions

## Tech Stack
- Frontend: Next.js (App Router), React, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui
- Backend: Python, FastAPI, SQLAlchemy, SQLite, WebSockets
- Video: WebRTC (Mesh Architecture)

## Coding Guidelines
1. Do not use external CSS files. Use Tailwind utility classes exclusively.
2. For the frontend, strictly adhere to the provided v0 design system tokens (e.g., bg-primary for the Zoom blue).
3. Do not introduce complex Authentication (JWT/OAuth). Assume a default user is always authenticated (ID: 1).
4. Keep all backend state (active WebSockets) in-memory for the MVP. Do not suggest Redis or Celery.
5. Prioritize functional, clean, modular React components over heavily animated or overly complex DOM structures.
6. When writing FastAPI endpoints, always use Pydantic schemas for request/response validation.